text_run.content: Understanding how to filter your search results by the proximity of entities is crucial in vector operations. A range search serves this exact purpose by narrowing down results according to the distance between a
vector and vectors. This guide will walk you through the process of conducting a range search in Zilliz Cloud, which consists of a vector similarity search followed by distance-based filtering.
The support for range search is available as a Beta feature. The feature and the documentation may change anytime during the Beta stage.
Before conducting a range search, make sure the following conditions are met:
You have upgraded your cluster to the Beta version.
You have downloaded the example dataset. For details, see
You have created a collection with a schema matching the example dataset and inserted data into the collection. For details, see
Quick steps for a range search
: Initiate by ensuring your dataset is loaded and ready for search.
parameters to control your search precision. Zilliz Cloud provides
metric types for distance measuring. The configuration of
is affected by the metric type used for distance measuring.
: Perform the range search using the parameters set in step 2. The vectors returned will be within the range you specified, tailored to the distance metrics you have chosen.

# conduct a range search
query_vector = rows[0]['title_vector']

res = collection.search(
    data=[query_vector],
    anns_field="title_vector",
    param=search_params,
    output_fields=["title", "link"],
    limit=100,
)

ids = [ hits.ids for hits in res ]

print(ids)
